cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as question answering. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach to improve the performance of memory networks. It may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves selecting relevant information from a large pool of data and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for reasoning and attention mechanisms.
